Is there a way to say something like

```typescript
import { SignOptions } from 'electron-osx-sign';

// ...
interface ElectronOsxSignOptions extends SignOptions {
  identity?: string | true;
}
```

and have `identity` get overridden properly by TypeScript? Personally I'd rather have as little copypasta as possible.

@malept is that valid typescript? See this question in [stackoverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41285211/overriding-interface-property-type-defined-in-typescript-d-ts-file)

What about once the types get published:

```typescript
import { SignOptions } from 'electron-osx-sign';

interface ElectronOsxSignOptions extends Omit<SignOptions, 'identity'>  {
  identity?: string | true;
}
```
